body:
Hi guys.

Just starting to work with honeybee and I keep geeting this error when I try to label surfaces:



1. Solution exception:'Brep' object has no attribute 'Surfaces'



I even get it with the example files but I think everything is alredy updated so I don't know what I'm missing. Any idea?



Thanks guys

PS: Files attached
topic: HoneyBee LabelSurface: 'Brep' object has no attribute 'Surfaces'

replies.body: Your file works fine with me: [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/phdCK*jNYvGLHsObN6482btxNR5wo9dzxkxDGb5O8t4f8auTOCiDyxNm9gxV8Kne5xcXOS6QeH222PXGxB*c3PL345IIiJLz/Capture.JPG) -A.

Yeah... I assume it has to do with my installation or my computer.. But no idea what it might be.

Any idea?

Might be a long shot, but perhaps you're running an old Rhino Service Release in which RhinoCommon does not have the [Brep.Surfaces](http://developer.rhino3d.com/api/RhinoCommonWin/html/P_Rhino_Geometry_Brep_Surfaces.htm) property yet (admittedly, sounds like a long shot, but perhaps).

Actually that worked! I was using an outdated SR.

Thanks a lot!
